  'compound-interest-calculator': ['Compound growth applies each period\'s return to the principal and previously accumulated growth. Contributions add a second stream of deposits that can compound for different lengths of time.', 'At 5% annual growth, $1,000 compounded annually becomes $1,050 after one year and $1,102.50 after two years, before fees and taxes.', 'A fixed return is an illustration, not a forecast. Actual investments fluctuate, and fees, taxes, inflation, and contribution timing change real outcomes.'],
  'loan-payment-calculator': ['A standard fixed-payment loan uses an amortization formula. Each payment includes interest on the remaining balance and principal that reduces that balance.', 'A higher rate or shorter term usually raises the monthly payment. A longer term can lower the payment while increasing total interest paid.', 'Real quotes can include origination charges, insurance, taxes, variable rates, balloon payments, and rounding rules not represented by a basic estimate.'],
